The paper deals with spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the practical implementation of the proposed method, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with system-wide failure, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the comparison of the proposed method with traditional approaches, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses theoretical analysis to support the claims of detection performance, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
